@Node History "NetInput - History"
@next Author
@prev Future

  @{b}Development history of "netinput"@{ub}

  Release 37.3

    ñ Unfortunately, the description of the IGNOREMOUSEMOVE option of
      the netinput client program was wrong. It stated erraneously that
      the named parameter would control a number of mouse moves to be
      melted instead of determining a time interval. I apologize deeply to
      all those who got problems out of this embarrassing mistake.
      Remember: Never write a documentation in such a hurry 8^(

  Release 37.2

    ñ User part of Installation erranously stated to add netinputd as
      a "nowait" daemon, however it is of type "wait"
    ñ minor server cleanup

  Release 37.1

    ñ initial release

  @{b}Technical history of "netinput"@{ub}

  For more technical details, please refer to the source code. In the
  header section of each source file, you find the pseudo-keyword
  $HISTORY: after which follows the complete revision history of this
  file.

@EndNode

